Step 1: Update Your System
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

Step 2: Uninstall Old Versions (if any)
sudo apt remove docker docker-engine docker.io containerd runc

Step 3: Install Required Dependencies
sudo apt install apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl software-properties-common -y

Step 4: Add Dockerâ€™s Official GPG Key
curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg

Step 5: Add the Docker Repository
echo \
  "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/docker-archive-keyring.gpg] \
  https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
  $(lsb_release -cs) stable" | \
  sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null

Step 6: Update Package Index (again)
sudo apt update

Step 7: Install Docker Engine, CLI, and Containerd
sudo apt install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io -y

Step 8: Verify Docker Installation
docker --version

Step 9: Enable and Start Docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
(Press q to exit the status screen)

Step 11 (Optional): Run Docker Without sudo

By default, Docker commands require sudo.
To run without it:

sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
Then log out and log back in, or run:
newgrp docker

Now test:
docker ps
